{
  "doc_id": "37218",
  "text": "In Russia, about 0·5% of the population is incarcerated. However, prisoners accounted for 27% of tuberculosis cases in 1995. [CITATION_1] Since then, Russia has focused on addressing tuberculosis in prisons, enforcing both mandatory screening and directly observed treatment. [CITATION_2] These policies have been credited with reducing the proportion of tuberculosis cases that were detected in prisons to 12% in 2004.",
